⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Lotka–Volterra
node POP · POP · ⟦Lotka–Volterra:POP:346524⟧

WHO   — Lotka–Volterra — predator & prey, oscillating
WHAT  — The dance: prey rise, predators follow and crash them, predators starve and fall, prey rise again — the lynx-hare cycle.
WHERE — POP · Population Dynamics  Framework inputs: ecology, epidemiology, population genetics; Asimov's Foundation; verified & cited  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0 · Life Science)
WHY   — Because populations are not alone; they eat and are eaten, and the coupling makes cycles.
HOW   — By tying each population's growth to the other's size, producing closed, lagging oscillations.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Prey peaks, then predator peaks, then both crash and rise again. I am the cycle — though real lynx and hares are messier than I am.

